 <text>
  <front>
   <head>On leaving Bath.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">, in their Nature shy,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">View Strangers with a distant Eye:</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">We think them partial and severe;</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And judge their Manners by their Air:</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Are undeceiv'd by Time alone;</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Their Value rises, as they're known.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">many a worthy Mind I found,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">With Sense and Taste, by Virtue crown'd,</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">At once so truly good and great,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">They knew to bear a prosp'rous State.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">take from noble Blood Pretence</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">To act or look with Insolence:</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Veins, with the richest Purple dy'd,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But seldom swell the Heart with Pride,</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">So, tho' the River-Gods, from high,</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">With plenteous Urns the Streams supply,</l>
     <l n="17" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Which still enlarge, as they descend,</l>
     <l n="18" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Roll down, and in the Ocean end,</l>
     <l n="19" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Thro' Ages pour'd; yet, to our Eyes,</l>
     <l n="20" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Old Ocean is too great to rise.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="21" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">gen'rous Treatment I have met,</l>
     <l n="22" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Hath run me deep in  Debt:</l>
     <l n="23" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And, could my artless Lines impart</l>
     <l n="24" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The grateful Dictates of my Heart,</l>
     <l n="25" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Latest Posterity should know</l>
     <l n="26" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The Sense I have of what I owe.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="5" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="27" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">, a long, a last Adieu!</l>
     <l n="28" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Since I no more shall visit you;</l>
     <l n="29" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Nor fix'd by Choice, but barr'd by Fate,</l>
     <l n="30" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">From a Felicity so great.</l>
     <l n="31" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">O may thy Waters ever be</l>
     <l n="32" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Healthful to others, as to me!</l>
     <l n="33" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Had , with prophetic View,</l>
     <l n="34" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Beheld the Wonders wrought by you,</l>
     <l n="35" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Arts he might have spar'd,</l>
     <l n="36" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And Life by thee alone repair'd.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
